    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 87.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    120, diplomatic series, of the 7th ultimo, in regard to recent political changes
                    in Korea.</p>
                <p>Your action in refusing to recognize that Korean independence dates from the 6th
                    of June, 1895, is approved. The position assumed by this Government toward Korea
                    since contracting a treaty with it in 1882 has in no wise been affected by
                    recent events. Korea’s treaty independence since then has been for us an
                    established and accepted fact.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
